          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>6289</commentid>
            <who name="Christian Hagendorn">christian.hagendorn</who>
            <bug_when>2008-11-13 19:02:00 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The IE8 has a strange rendering problem in IE8 standard mode. You can click wild in the HTML view (developer tool IE8) without changing style. The content (text, icons, buttons, etc.) jumps in the IE8 view.

I think that there is a rendering problem, so we will wait for the next IE8 release, before we test more. You can run Qooxdoo without problems in IE7 standard and quirks mode in IE8, by setting the meta tag or request header. </thetext>
          </long_desc>
